VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \bsystem\s*\(\s*["'].*(/bin|/usr/bin)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:validate|check|verify && MISSING:test|example|sample
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the use of `system()` with hardcoded file paths that may introduce security risks.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Use of `system()` with Hardcoded Paths.
